class=\"fn\">grad'</span> <span class=\"fn\">u</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">grad</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">grad'</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./PhysLean/Mathematics/VariationalCalculus/HasVarGradient.html#HasVarGradientAt.unique","kind":"theorem","line":153,"name":"HasVarGradientAt.unique","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L153-L159"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Mathematics/VariationalCalculus/HasVarGradient.html#«termδ(_:=_),∫_,_»\"><span class=\"name\">«termδ(_:=_),∫_,_»</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">Lean.ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The variational gradient of a function `F : (X → U) → (X → ℝ)` evaluated\nat a function `u : X → U`.\n\nThis not defined defined for a functional `S : (X → U) → ℝ` but rather for the function\n`F : (X → U) → (X → ℝ)` which is the integrand of the functional `S u = ∫ x, F (u x) x ∂μ`.\nFor example for action integral, `S u = ∫ t, L (u t) (deriv u t)` we have\n`S' u t = L (u t) (deriv u t)`.\n\nOn functions `F : (X → U) → (X → ℝ)` which do not have a variational gradient,\nthis function is defined to give `0`.\n","docLink":"./PhysLean/Mathematics/VariationalCalculus/HasVarGradient.html#«termδ(_:=_),∫_,_»","kind":"def","line":143,"name":"«termδ(_:=_),∫_,_»","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L143-L144"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Mathematics/VariationalCalculus/HasVarGradient.html#«termδ_,∫_,_»\"><span class=\"name\">«termδ_,∫_,_»</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">Lean.ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The variational gradient of a function `F : (X → U) → (X → ℝ)` evaluated\nat a function `u : X → U`.\n\nThis not defined defined for a functional `S : (X → U) → ℝ` but rather for the function\n`F : (X → U) → (X → ℝ)` which is the integrand of the functional `S u = ∫ x, F (u x) x ∂μ`.\nFor example for action integral, `S u = ∫ t, L (u t) (deriv u t)` we have\n`S' u t = L (u t) (deriv u t)`.\n\nOn functions `F : (X → U) → (X → ℝ)` which do not have a variational gradient,\nthis function is defined to give `0`.\n","docLink":"./PhysLean/Mathematics/VariationalCalculus/HasVarGradient.html#«termδ_,∫_,_»","kind":"def","line":139,"name":"«termδ_,∫_,_»","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L139-L140"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">noncomputable def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Mathematics/VariationalCalculus/HasVarGradient.html#varGradient\"><span class=\"name\">varGradient</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">X</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Basic.html#NormedAddCommGroup\">NormedAddCommGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Module/Basic.html#NormedSpace\">NormedSpace</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/MeasureSpaceDef.html#MeasureTheory.MeasureSpace\">MeasureTheory.MeasureSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">U</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Basic.html#NormedAddCommGroup\">NormedAddCommGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">U</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Module/Basic.html#NormedSpace\">NormedSpace</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">U</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./PhysLean/Mathematics/InnerProductSpace/Basic.html#InnerProductSpace'\">InnerProductSpace'</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">U</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">F</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">X</span> → <span class=\"fn\">U</span>)</span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">X</span> → <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">u</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">X</span> → <span class=\"fn\">U</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">X</span> → <span class=\"fn\">U</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The variational gradient of a function `F : (X → U) → (X → ℝ)` evaluated\nat a function `u : X → U`.\n\nThis not defined defined for a functional `S : (X → U) → ℝ` but rather for the function\n`F : (X → U) → (X → ℝ)` which is the integrand of the functional `S u = ∫ x, F (u x) x ∂μ`.\nFor example for action integral, `S u = ∫ t, L (u t) (deriv u t)` we have\n`S' u t = L (u t) (deriv u t)`.\n\nOn functions `F : (X → U) → (X → ℝ)` which do not have a variational gradient,\nthis function is defined to give `0`.\n","docLink":"./PhysLean/Mathematics/VariationalCalculus/HasVarGradient.html#varGradient","kind":"def","line":120,"name":"varGradient","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L120-L136"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Mathematics/VariationalCalculus/HasVarGradient.html#HasVarGradientAt.neg\"><span class=\"name\">HasVarGradientAt</span>.<span class=\"name\">neg</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">X</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Basic.html#NormedAddCommGroup\">NormedAddCommGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Module/Basic.html#NormedSpace\">NormedSpace</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/MeasureSpaceDef.html#MeasureTheory.MeasureSpace\">MeasureTheory.MeasureSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">U</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn